<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="388" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">504.418B1/212</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1284</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-03">September 3,
                                1935</date>.<lb/>[Received September 17.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of the Department’s instruction No. 523 of August 2nd regarding
                            the adherence of all the nations of the world to the Roerich Pact and to
                            inform the Department that in the course of a conversation with an
                            official of the Italian Ministry of Foreign Affairs I inquired as to the
                            view with which the Italian Government might be disposed to regard the
                            Pact.</p>
                        <p>I shall not fail to communicate to the Department the expression of the
                            attitude of the Italian Government as soon as it is received.<note n="7" xml:id="d388fn7">No further communication on this subject from the
                                Italian Government was reported by the American Embassy.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Alexander Kirk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>